This should be restricted when the Intel-cpu option is not enabled.
Done, but please let me know if there is some meson-specific way to do it better.
Done

Is there a reason this is necessary?  Ideally we can use a common .clang-tidy file across the project, but things like this make it harder.

I suspect you're just missing a .clang-tidy-ignore in subprojects.
(This can be addressed in a follow-up)

Looks like clang-tidy-ignore is not supported for OpenBMC CI: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/openbmc-build-scripts/+/53234
Furthermore, when (if) it is merged - it will check only source files, not headers
We didn't take this commit from LeiYu because it is built into Meson now.

I see. But anyway are you sure there is a way to ignore header file using clang-tidy-ignore? Could you please point out how to fill in the file so that it ignores peci.h? 
clang-tidy-ignore doesn't seem to be standard clang feature - instead this file seem to be parsed by a specific CI infrastructure individually. 
I can't find its usage in meson source codes, but whenever such approach is used - it is said to check (or ignore) only source files.

See https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/dbus-sensors/+/63162

Feel free to squash some or all of this into your commit.

Thank you for sharing it! Looks like it works. Cherry-picked libpeci related changes to the patchset.
I would abstain from squashing peci-ioctl.h changes to this patchset since it is different subject.
Done
